with (at least) the following in the commit message:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This closes #5661&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;commit e9711a61be0c260629c9f2f34c03af6e1aa9ac61&lt;br/&gt;
Author: Nico Kruber &amp;lt;nico@...&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date:   2018-03-08T11:22:32Z&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-8896&quot; title=&quot;Kafka08Fetcher trying to look up topic &amp;quot;n/a&amp;quot; on partiton &amp;quot;-1&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-8896&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-8896&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;kafka08&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; remove all cancel MARKERs before trying to find partition leaders&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This guards us against #cancel() being called multiple times and then trying to&lt;br/&gt;
    look up an invalid topic/partition pair.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;commit bffe96f5e3522824656ed55074ac09591a36e2ae&lt;br/&gt;
Author: Nico Kruber &amp;lt;nico@...&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date:   2018-03-08T11:23:47Z&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;hotfix&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;kafka&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; do not run cancel() in the discovery loop if already cancelled&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;</comment>
